## Module Content

Modules support two mutually exclusive attributes for content:

- **`content_file`** (recommended) - Points to a local file path. Avoids storing content in state, preventing state file bloat.
- **`content_base64`** - Inline base64-encoded content. Primarily used after importing.

**Import Behavior:** When importing, Terraform always populates `content_base64` in state. If your config uses `content_file`, an in-place update will switch state to use `content_file` (assuming content matches).

